The paper deals with the development of a system for autonomous UAV navigation and landing in disaster-struck environments. This involves the use of computer vision techniques for identifying safe landing regions on debris piles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these are the primary areas of focus in the paper. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms for landing site detection, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also deals with the use of UAVs in real-world scenarios, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
